    "methodology": "Discharge delay figures are from the NHS England Daily Discharge Situation Report. The data covers patients in acute trusts who do not meet the criteria to reside (i.e. are medically fit but cannot be discharged). The methodology was expanded in May 2024 to include all patients delayed by at least one day (previously 7+ days only). CQC ratings are the latest overall rating for each adult social care location in England. Spending figures are in 2023-24 prices (real terms), covering local authority adult social care net current expenditure. Unpaid carers data is from the 2021 Census.",
